✅ Find Missing and Repeated Values in a Grid

Input:
grid = [[9,1,7],
        [8,9,2],
        [3,4,6]]

Repeated = 9
Missing = 5

Output: [9,5]

## HashSet Approach

### Complexity
Time Complexity: O(n²)
Space Complexity: O(n²)

class Solution {
    public int[] findMissingAndRepeatedValues(int[][] grid) {

        int n = grid.length;
        Set<Integer> set = new HashSet<>();

        int repeated = -1;

        for (int[] row : grid) {
            for (int num : row) {
                if (!set.add(num)) {
                    repeated = num;
                }
            }
        }

        int missing = -1;

        for (int i = 1; i <= n * n; i++) {
            if (!set.contains(i)) {
                missing = i;
                break;
            }
        }

        return new int[]{repeated, missing};
    }
}

